# üì± Termux-Seismo
![](./art.jpeg)
A lightweight Node.js server that turns your rooted OnePlus 8 (or any Termux-capable Android) into a live seismograph.

## Installation

1Ô∏è‚É£ **Install dependencies on Termux**

```bash
pkg update -y
pkg install -y nodejs-lts git termux-api
npm i -g nodemon
```

Also install the companion Termux:API app from F-Droid.

2Ô∏è‚É£ **Clone and set up**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/you/termux-seismo.git
cd termux-seismo
cp .env.example .env
npm install
```

3Ô∏è‚É£ **Configure .env**

```dotenv
# Duration of rolling history (minutes)
MAX_HISTORY_MINUTES=60

# Sampling interval (ms)
SAMPLE_INTERVAL_MS=200

# Web server port
PORT=3000
```

4Ô∏è‚É£ **Run it**

Dev mode:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Or production:

```bash
npm start
```

Then visit: `http://127.0.0.1:7070/` (or whatever you set the port as).

## üìä Data Storage

- Sensor data is saved to `data/seismo.json`.
- Each record:

```json
{ "t": 1696262801000, "x": -0.02, "y": 9.78, "z": -0.14, "g": 9.79, "a": 0.02 }
```

- Records older than `MAX_HISTORY_MINUTES` are automatically deleted.![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
